symc.name: SERVICE_ERROR_CRITICAL
symc.desc: The startup program logs the error in the event log, if possible. If the last-known-good configuration is being started, the startup operation fails. Otherwise, the system is restarted with the last-known good configuration.

symc.name: SERVICE_ERROR_IGNORE
symc.desc: The startup program ignores the error and continues the startup operation.

symc.name: SERVICE_ERROR_NORMAL
symc.desc: The startup program logs the error in the event log but continues the startup operation.

symc.name: SERVICE_ERROR_SEVERE
symc.desc: The startup program logs the error in the event log. If the last-known-good configuration is being started, the startup operation continues. Otherwise, the system is restarted with the last-known-good configuration.
